  - key: ''
    value: The Master's role as Judicial Officer of the Korean Royal Household was a position created during the exile of King Zhongxuan to the western territories to oversee Korean affairs in the Yuan court.
  - key: ''
    value: The Master's criticism of the historical treatment of the Empress Wu (武則天) demonstrates his commitment to moral principles in historical writing—he believed wrongdoers should be marked as such regardless of their position, a principle later vindicated when Zhu Xi similarly classified her as a usurper.
